cx CLI\par
\par
This software is a customized distribution based on openai/codex.\par
\par
The upstream openai/codex project is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.\par
A copy of the upstream license is available at:\par
https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/main/LICENSE\par
\par
By installing this software you agree to the terms of the upstream Apache 2.0 license\par
and any additional terms provided by the distributor of this build.\par
\par
The installer will:\par
\par
1. Install cx.exe to the folder you choose (default: %LOCALAPPDATA%\\Programs\\cx).\par
2. Add that folder to your user PATH so that a new terminal can run "cx" directly.\par
3. Write a default configuration to %USERPROFILE%\\.codex\\config.toml if you do not\par
   already have one (existing configuration is never overwritten).\par
\par
This is a per-user installation and does not require administrator privileges.\par
